ed, the bytecode emitter converts it to executable bytecode. This is the core compilation stage.\n\n**Bytecode Emitter:**\n- **`js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.h`**: Bytecode emitter class (lines 77-150+ contain comprehensive documentation about the bytecode emission process, bytecode structures, control flow handling, and scope management)\n- **`js/src/frontend/BytecodeEmitter.cpp`**: Complete bytecode emitter implementation (line 158 shows the constructor initialization)\n\nThe `BytecodeEmitter` class:\n1. Traverses the ParseNode tree\n2. Emits JSOp bytecode instructions (defined in `vm/Opcodes.h`)\n3. Manages bytecode sections for prologue and main code\n4. Handles jump patching for control flow (if/else, loops, try/catch)\n5. Manages variable scopes and bindings\n6. Generates source notes for debugging\n\n**Supporting Bytecode Components:**\n- **`js/src/frontend/BytecodeSection.h`**: Bytecode section management\n- **`js/src/frontend/BytecodeOffset.h`**: Bytecode offset tracking\n- **`js/src/frontend/SourceNotes.h`/`.cpp`**: Source note generation for debugging information\n- **`js/src/frontend/JumpList.h`**: Jump list management for forward jumps\n- **`js/src/frontend/EmitterScope.h`**: Scope binding information during emission\n\n**Bytecode Output Structure:**\n- **`js/src/frontend/Stencil.h`**: Compilation stencil structure (intermediate representation before JSScript creation)\n- **`js/src/frontend/CompilationStencil.h`**: Extended stencil with metadata\n\n## Stage 6: JSScript Creation (Bytecode Output)\n\nThe final bytecode output is encapsulated in a JSScript object:\n\n**JSScript (The Bytecode Container):**\n- **`js/src/vm/JSScript.h`** (line 1787): Defines the `JSScript` class which is the primary bytecode container. JSScript inherits from `js::BaseScript` and contains:\n  - The bytecode array (`jsbytecode* code`)\n  - Script metadata (line numbers, source location, function information)\n  - Scope and binding information\n  - JIT compilation data\n  - Debug information\n  - Source notes for mapping bytecode back to source\n\nThe JSScript structure contains all necessary information for:\n- Interpretation of bytecode\n- JIT compilation (Ion, Baseline)\n- Debugging and profiling\n- Exception handling\n- Source mapping\n\n## Compilation Flow Summary\n\n1. **Entry**: `JS::Compile()` called with source text and compile options\n2. **Driver**: `CompileGlobalScript()` creates a `ScriptCompiler` instance\n3. **Tokenization**: TokenStream parses source into tokens\n4. **Parsing**: `Parser::parse()` generates ParseNode AST from tokens\n5. **Emission**: `BytecodeEmitter` traverses AST and generates bytecode\n6. **Stencil**: Bytecode and metadata collected in `CompilationStencil`\n7. **Instantiation**: `InstantiateStencils()` creates final `JSScript` object\n8. **Output**: `JSScript*` returned with executable bytecode ready for execution\n\n## Key Interconnections\n\n- **Parser ↔ SharedContext**: Parser uses SharedContext to track scope and compilation state\n- **ParseNode ↔ BytecodeEmitter**: BytecodeEmitter imports and traverses ParseNode trees\n- **BytecodeEmitter ↔ BytecodeSection**: Emitter writes bytecode to BytecodeSection\n- **Stencil ↔ JSScript**: Stencil is instantiated to create JSScript with GC-allocated objects\n\n## Supporting Infrastructure\n\n**Parsing Utilities:**\n- **`js/src/frontend/ParserAtom.h`**: Parser atoms (interned strings) for efficient name handling\n- **`js/src/frontend/UsedNameTracker.h`**: Tracking which names are used in scopes\n- **`js/src/frontend/Token.h`**: Token definitions\n- **`js/src/frontend/ErrorReporter.h`**: Error reporting during parsing\n\n**Bytecode Utilities:**\n- **`vm/Opcodes.h`**: JSOp bytecode operation definitions\n- **`vm/BytecodeUtil.h`**: Bytecode utility functions\n- **`vm/BytecodeIterator.h`**: Iterator for traversing bytecode sequences\n\nThis multi-stage pipeline enables SpiderMonkey to efficiently compile JavaScript to bytecode that can be executed by the interpreter or further optimized by JIT compilers.\n"
